# React Component Patterns

## Component Structure
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Implement proper prop validation
- Use functional components with hooks
- Follow the single responsibility principle

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS classes consistently
- Follow the existing design system
- Use responsive design patterns (grid, flexbox)
- Implement hover states and transitions

## Common Patterns

### Item Display Components
- Use [ItemCard.tsx](mdc:src/components/ItemCard.tsx) as reference
- Include image handling with Next.js Image component
- Show price formatting with `toFixed(2)`
- Implement proper link navigation

### Form Components
- Use controlled components with useState
- Implement proper form validation
- Show loading states during submission
- Use modal patterns for forms (see [ItemForm.tsx](mdc:src/components/admin/ItemForm.tsx))

### Filter Components
- Use dropdown/select elements for filtering
- Implement cascading dropdowns (ConsoleType â†’ Console)
- Reset dependent selections when parent changes

## Props Interface Pattern
```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  // Required props first
  requiredProp: string
  // Optional props with default values
  optionalProp?: string
  // Event handlers
  onSubmit: (data: any) => void
  onCancel: () => void
}
```